    <text>
        <title type="main" xml:lang="fr">Adieux à Suzon</title>
        <title type="sub" xml:lang="fr"> mélodie</title>

        <div xml:id="summary">
            <div xml:id="contents">
                <p> [Incipit] <measure quantity="210" units="bars">210 </measure>bars</p>

                <p>high key is D, low key is unknown</p>
            </div>
            <div xml:id="instrumentation">
                <p>tenor or soprano and piano baritone or contralto and piano</p>
            </div>



            <div xml:id="composition">
                <head>Poem:</head><p> by <author>Alfred de Musset</author> (<date>1810–57</date>),
                        <title xml:lang="fr">Adieux à Suzon</title>, first published in the <title
                        xml:lang="fr">Revue de Paris</title> in <date>May 1852</date> and collected
                    in the <date>1852</date> edition of his <title xml:lang="fr">Poésies
                    nouvelles</title>. ‘Suzon’ was the daughter of the préfet of the Vosges, M. de
                    la Bergerie, when de Musset was visiting in <date>1845</date></p>.
                    <head>Composition:</head>
                <p><date type="composition">September 1866 </date>for publication by Heugel in
                        <title xml:lang="fr">Feuilles d’album</title>. </p>
                <head>Dedicatee:</head>
                <p> Hermann Léon (<date>1814–1858</date>) was a baritone, who sang at the Opéra and
                    the Opéra-Comique, but the dedication must be to his son, whose career is
                    unknown.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="autograph">
            <head>Autograph score: </head>
            <p>not known</p>
        </div>

